children.desc:
External pull-up give SP control of restarting. 
Falling edge triggers restart function which tags 2-25sec 
(default 10s) set by PMBus registers. 10us glitch filter at ADM1272.
Writing to this will cause a strobe that exceeds the glitch filter
timing and will self-clear (note actual output is inverted to meet
circuit's active low requirement
A0 Group power enable (starts state machine)

NIC CLD_RST control. Controls CLD_RST_N (inverted). Defaults to reset asserted to be
cleared by software when SP3 hotplug indicates enable

Input from ADM1272. Rising edge enable PMBus OPERATION on
command or PMBus POWER_CYCLE required to clear, assuming all
faults are clear. (Inverted to active high in register)

From ADUM1272. Asserted when PWGIN > thresh, enable pin is
high and UVx and OV pins are in-range, no actuive fault conditons 
and mosfet is fully enhanced (Vgs > 10V).

Input from ADM1272. Rising edge enable PMBus OPERATION on 
command or PMBus POWER_CYCLE required to clear, assuming all faults 
are clear.

Readback for V1P5_SP_VDD_RTC_A1 rail.
(SP3_TO_SEQ_RTC_V1P5_EN - a poor net name)

SP3_TO_SP_SLP_S3 inversion of signal from AMD CPU, Used
at beginning of GroupB state machine

SP3_TO_SP_SLP_S5 inversion of signal from AMD CPU, Used 
at beginning of GroupB state machine

Asserted by AMD after PWR_GOOD is asserted by sequencer 
should be here in: min 15ms, max of 20.4ms(SP3_TO_SEQ_PWROK_V3P3 net)

Asserted (and inverted) from AMD's RESET_L pin. 10Ms minimum assertion time, 
remains asserted for minimum of 1ms after PWROK assertion
(SP3_TO_SEQ_RESET_V3P3_L net)

Readback from VDD_MEM_ABCD_A0 rail (PWR_CONT1_SP3_PG1)
Power good 1 for RA229618 (U350) is configured for 
VDD_MEM_ABCD_A0

Readback from VDD_MEM_EFGH_A0 rail (PWR_CONT2_SP3_PG1)
Power good 1 for RA229618 (U351) is configured for 
VDD_MEM_EFGH_A0

Readback from V3P3_SYS_A0 rail (PWR_CONT_DIMM_ABCD_PG1)
PG1 from ISL68224 U352, should be configured to represent 
V3P3_SYS_A0 rail status
From ISL68224 U352. PWR_CONT_DIMM_ABCD_PG2 net. No defined function.
From ISL68224 U418. PWR_CONT_DIMM_EFGH_PG1 net. No defined function.
From ISL68224 U418. PWR_CONT_DIMM_EFGH_PG2 net. No defined function.

Set high (inverted from board) when rail reaches OT_WARN threshold, 
only valid after configuration (PWR_CONT1_SP3_NVRHOT net).
from RAA229618 U350 controlling SP3_VDD_VCORE_A0 and VDD_MEM_ABCD_A0 rails

Catastrophic fault protection output from RAA229618 U350 controlling 
SP3_VDD_VCORE_A0 and VDD_MEM_ABCD_A0 rails

Set high (inverted from board) when rail reaches OT_WARN threshold, only valid 
after configuration. From RAA229618 U351 driving rails SP3_VDDCR_SOC_A0 and 
VDD_MEM_EFGH_A0 (PWR_CONT2_SP3_NVRHOT net)

Catastrophic fault protection output from RAA229618 U351 controlling 
SP3_VDDCR_SOC_A0 and VDD_MEM_EFGH_A0 rails (PWR_CONT2_SP3_CFP net).

Power good 0 for RA229618 (U351) is configured for 
SP3_VDDCR_SOC_A0 (PWR_CONT2_SP3_PG0 net)

Power good 0 from RA229618 (U350) is configured for
SP3_VDD_VCORE_A0 (PWR_CONT1_SP3_PG0 net)
Power good for V1P1_NIC_ETH_IO_A0HP (inverted NIC_TO_SEQ_V1P1_PG_L net)
Power good for V1P2_NIC_MDIO_A0HP  (inverted NIC_TO_SEQ_V1P2_PG_L net)
Power good for V1P2_NIC_ETH  (inverted NIC_TO_SEQ_V1P2_PG_L net)
Power good for V1P5_NIC_AVDD_A0HP (inverted NIC_TO_SEQ_V1P5A_PG_L net)
Power good for V1P5_NIC_PCIE_MEM_A0HP (inverted NIC_TO_SEQ_V1P5D_PG_L net)
inverted CPU's thermtrip_L, 500ms to shut down power planes into S5 state. De-assertion of PWROK resets THERMTRIP_L
inverted FSR_REQ_L net. Maybe used in host reset detection, see RFD138. No defined use in power-up

Output from the AMD processor that it has effectively acknowledged that power is itself
good.  This  is  connected  from  the  BSP  to  the  AP's  PWR_GOOD  input  in  a  two  socket
system.  The  FCH  may  actually  control  this  being  generated  via  the
FCH::PM::RESETCONTROL2 register.
Enable for fan ADUM1272. (1us glitch filter at ADUM1272)

FANHP_RESTART pin (note actual output is inverted to meet
circuit's active low requirement, so a 1 here means a 0 on the board)

External pull-up give SP control of restarting. 
Falling edge triggers restart function which tags 2-25sec 
(default 10s) set by PMBus registers. 10us glitch filter at ADM1272.
Writing to this will cause a strobe that exceeds the glitch filter
timing and will self-clear (note actual output is inverted to meet
circuit's active low requirement

De-asserted to processor after GroupA supplies are stable (10ms after S5 rails minimum) 
(SEQ_TO_SP3_RSMRST_V3P3_L net inverted from this register)
GroupB1: Drives VPP_ABCD_A0 rail (pwr_cont_dimm_en0 net RevB)
GroupB1: Drives VPP_EFGH_A0 rail (pwr_cont_dimm_en1 net RevB)
GroupB1: Enables V3P3_SYS_A0 rail (seq_to_v3p3_sys_en net RevB)
GroupB1: Enables V1P8_SP3_VDD_18_A0 rail (seq_to_sp3_v1p8_en net RevB)
GroupB2: Enables VDD_MEM_ABCD_A0 rail (pwr_cont1_sp3_en net RevB)
GroupB2: Enables VDD_MEM_EFGH_A0 rail (pwr_cont2_sp3_en net RevB)
GroupB2: Enables VTT_ABCD_A0 rail (seq_to_vtt_abcd_en net RevB)
GroupB2: Enables VTT_EFGH_A0 rail (seq_to_vtt_efgh_en net RevB)

Strap High, no definition yet. PWROK pin to RAA229618 U350 driving 
SP3_VDD_VCORE_A0 and VDD_MEM_ABCD_A0

Strap High, no definition yet. PWROK pin to RAA229618 U351 driving
SP3_VDDCR_SOC_A0 and VDD_MEM_EFGH_A0 (PWR_CONT2_SP3_PWROK net)

Enable for RAA229618 (U35) VDD_MEM_EFGH_A0 (and gates SP3_VDDCR_SOC_A0) 
(PWR_CONT2_SP3_EN net)
Pulsed according to AMD's EDS min 15ms (SP_TO_SP3_PWR_BTN_L net, inverted from this register)
This is asserted to CPU, 1ms before asserting. Set when A0 rails are good. (SEQ_TO_SP3_PWR_GOOD net)
Turns on V1P2_NIC_ENET_A0HP, no readback (SEQ_TO_NIC_V1P2_ENET_EN net)
Input to FPGA from SP3 I/O expander (inverted)
Becomes clock enable for clk_100M_TO_RSW (SEQ_TO_NIC_COMB_PG net)
CLD Reset to Chelsio. De-asserted after NIC power stable (SEQ_TO_NIC_CLD_RST_L net inverted)
Alert SP3 of a NIC power fault (NIC_TO_SP3_PWRFLT_L inverted net)
NIC's EXT_RST_L output (inverted).  Active when NIC internals in reset
CPU's `SYS_RESET_L`, see EDS. 10ms assertion time, would traditionally be wired to a PC reset button

Debug ONLY. Setting this allows the A0 state machine to ingore SP3 handshakes.
This is potentially useful for power bringup but should not be used when a CPU is actually
installed

Nic debug control only. Seeting will force CLD_RST assert until cleared. When cleared,
CLD_RST will normally be controlled by state machine and NIC Control register

Nic debug control only. Setting will force Perst_L assert until cleared. When
cleared, PERST will normally be controlled by SP3 I/O expander. Set next bit PERST_FORCE_SOLO to
ignore all SP3 control and have this register directly control I/O regardless of SP3's PERST state
Nic debug control only. Make PERST ignore any SP3 I/O and drive directly from previous bit
CPU's `SYS_RESET_L`, see EDS. 10ms assertion time, would traditionally be wired to a PC reset button
Falling edge counter of AMD's reset output while in A0/A0HP. Saturates at 255. Any write clears
Falling edge counter of AMD's PowerOK output while in A0/A0HP. Saturates at 255.  Any write clears
